name: FInteriorSettings
doc: Struct encapsulating settings for interior areas.

ExteriorVolume: The desired volume of sounds outside the volume when the player is inside the volume
ExteriorTime: The time over which to interpolate from the current volume to the desired volume of sounds outside the volume when the player enters the volume
ExteriorLPF: The desired LPF frequency cutoff in hertz of sounds outside the volume when the player is inside the volume
ExteriorLPFTime: The time over which to interpolate from the current LPF to the desired LPF of sounds outside the volume when the player enters the volume
InteriorVolume: The desired volume of sounds inside the volume when the player is outside the volume
InteriorTime: The time over which to interpolate from the current volume to the desired volume of sounds inside the volume when the player exits the volume
InteriorLPF: The desired LPF frequency cutoff in hertz of sounds inside the volume when the player is outside the volume
InteriorLPFTime: The time over which to interpolate from the current LPF to the desired LPF of sounds inside the volume when the player exits the volume
